  <bioghist id="aspace_d9d1dbe09cdf08c05dc8484da35fc4af">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>William J. Cassidy compiled these materials in the course of researching and writing his doctoral dissertation, "The Tri-State Zinc-Lead Mining Region: Growth, Problems and Prospects" (University of Pittsburgh, 1955).</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_07aecd5c6cd2782d4938bfe3f5a77635">
    <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
<p>The collection contains letters and interview notes from persons involved in lead and zinc mining in the Tri-State Mining District (Kansas, Missouri, Oklahoma); describing early attempts at unionization, copies of contracts between operators and locals of International Union of Mine, Mill and Smelter Workers, CIO; printed ephemera from the union and several of its locals, mostly dating to the 1940s; clippings; mining industry and government pamphlets on mining conditions and a manuscript, "History of International Union of Mine, Mill and Smelter Workers Union Local 15," by Harry Blasser.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_cca30334ecbb5c8ce4ff6ead605fad71">
